enny which sheds light on his criminal past, leading him to suggest Shaun is being used by him.\n |LineColor       = A8C0D8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 17\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 17\n |Title           = Smile\n |DirectedBy      = Bill D'Elia\n |WrittenBy       = David Hoselton & Karen Struck\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|3|19}}\n |Viewers         = 9.03<ref name=\"1.17\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/monday-final-ratings-march-19-2018/|title='American Idol,' 'Good Girls,' all others hold: Monday final ratings|last=Porter|first=Rick|website=[[TV by the Numbers]]|date=March 20, 2018|access-date=March 20, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180321021430/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/monday-final-ratings-march-19-2018/|archive-date=March 21, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Shaun and Alex treat teenaged Gretchen's [[Mobius Syndrome|M\u00f6bius syndrome]], enabling her to smile; Andrews persuades an insurance executive to cover the surgery. After Gretchen fails to wake up, it is believed that she has become brain dead, but Park realizes that a rare condition is causing her to remain under anesthesia and she recovers. Morgan and Claire's patient, \"Lucy Callard,\" is actually an [[identity theft|identity thief]] who let her insurance lapse to pay her son's college tuition and failed to fill her post-operative antibiotic prescription due to fear of discovery, resulting in a post-op infection. Morgan convinces the real Lucy Callard, a [[analgesic|painkiller]] addict, to enter rehab; Claire gains the trust of the imposter, Beatrice, who dies after her infection turns into [[sepsis]] that fails to respond to treatment. Jared romantically pursues his burn-victim patient, Celez, after she completes her treatment; he is also offered a job in Denver. Kenny takes advantage of Shaun. Shaun urges Glassman to date hospital barista Debbie; they hit it off over their interest in [[classic ca